<node CREATED="1372828708974" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1546772828" MODIFIED="1379745625966" TEXT="&#xb6; 1">
<node CREATED="1372828752567" ID="ID_1340121294" MODIFIED="1372880454602" TEXT="Variables and objects such as pairs, strings, vectors, and bytevectors implicitly denote locations or sequences of locations. "/>
<node CREATED="1372880454605" ID="ID_1182753594" MODIFIED="1372880459698" TEXT="A string, for example, denotes as many locations as there are characters in the string. "/>
<node CREATED="1372880459699" ID="ID_703929751" MODIFIED="1372908381750">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      A new value can be stored into one of these locations using the <font face="Courier">string-set!</font>&#xa0; procedure, but the string continues to denote the same locations as before.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372828711366" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_126191758" MODIFIED="1379745756133" TEXT="&#xb6; 2">
<node CREATED="1372828758978" ID="ID_1533156520" MODIFIED="1372908579415">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      An object fetched from a location,
    </p>
