</node>
<node CREATED="1372908819022" ID="ID_1964426464" MODIFIED="1372908825085" TEXT="All objects created by the other procedures listed in this report are mutable. "/>
<node CREATED="1372908825085" ID="ID_338465246" MODIFIED="1372909362043" TEXT="It is an error to attempt to store a new value into a location that is denoted by an immutable object.">
<icon BUILTIN="messagebox_warning"/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372828728333" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_505213903" MODIFIED="1379745956287" TEXT="&#xb6; 6">
<node CREATED="1372828780882" ID="ID_52429727" MODIFIED="1372909030682" TEXT="These locations are to be understood as conceptual, not physical. "/>
<node CREATED="1372909030683" ID="ID_1774659309" MODIFIED="1372909037766" TEXT="Hence, they do not necessarily correspond to memory addresses, and even if they do, the memory address might not be constant."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372828730301" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_845665596" MODIFIED="1379745958766" TEXT="&#xb6; 7">
<node CREATED="1372828791201" ID="ID_10387038" MODIFIED="1372909247152">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <i>Rationale</i>:&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
<node CREATED="1372909224444" ID="ID_809722732" MODIFIED="1372909256824" TEXT="In many systems it is desirable for ">
<node CREATED="1372909273750" ID="ID_440204" MODIFIED="1372909289662" TEXT="">
<node CREATED="1372909256825" ID="ID_692359983" MODIFIED="1372909266955" TEXT="constants "/>
<node CREATED="1372909266955" ID="ID_1659149753" MODIFIED="1372909271671" TEXT="(i.e. the values of literal expressions) "/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372909271671" ID="ID_1393637935" MODIFIED="1372909271673" TEXT="to reside in read-only memory. "/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372909046913" ID="ID_231996531" MODIFIED="1372909371103" TEXT="Making it an error to alter constants permits this implementation strategy, ">
<icon BUILTIN="messagebox_warning"/>
<node CREATED="1372909310428" ID="ID_1856699946" MODIFIED="1372909318079" TEXT="while not requiring other systems to distinguish between ">
<node CREATED="1372909318082" ID="ID_1246858970" MODIFIED="1372909324575" TEXT="mutable "/>
<node CREATED="1372909324575" ID="ID_496408797" MODIFIED="1372909324577" TEXT="and immutable objects."/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1371765576150" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_509546638" MODIFIED="1379746272188" TEXT="3.5 Proper tail recursion">
<node CREATED="1372909447483" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1141491678" MODIFIED="1379746065507" TEXT="&#xb6; 1">
<node CREATED="1372909475729" ID="ID_775126270" MODIFIED="1372972867585">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Implementations of Scheme are required to be <font color="#ff0000"><i>properly tail-recursive</i></font>.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372972354397" ID="ID_1571488080" MODIFIED="1372972906801">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Procedure calls that occur in certain syntactic contexts defined below are <font color="#ff0000"><i>tail calls</i></font>.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372972359622" ID="ID_1508336576" MODIFIED="1372972371567" TEXT="A Scheme implementation is properly tail-recursive if it supports an unbounded number of active tail calls. "/>
<node CREATED="1372972371570" ID="ID_1110734532" MODIFIED="1372972942998">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      A call is <font color="#ff0000"><i>active</i></font>&#xa0;if the called procedure might still return.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372972376216" ID="ID_670284514" MODIFIED="1372994160298">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Note that this includes calls that might be returned from
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
<node CREATED="1372994103321" ID="ID_1295980190" MODIFIED="1372994107322" TEXT="">
<node CREATED="1372994079081" ID="ID_1315649947" MODIFIED="1372994088364">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      either by the current continuation
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372994088367" ID="ID_1864727078" MODIFIED="1372994097145">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      or by continuations captured earlier by <font face="Courier">call-with-current-continuation</font>&#xa0;&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372994097147" ID="ID_1277455283" MODIFIED="1372994097151">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      that are later invoked.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372972393878" ID="ID_1061955377" MODIFIED="1372972402593" TEXT="In the absence of captured continuations, calls could return at most once and the active calls would be those that had not yet returned. "/>
<node CREATED="1372972402596" ID="ID_1792265623" MODIFIED="1379295579239" TEXT="A formal definition of proper tail recursion can be found in [6].">
<icon BUILTIN="messagebox_warning"/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372909450268" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_434208830" MODIFIED="1379746096767" TEXT="&#xb6; 2">
<node CREATED="1372909481897" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_521231617" MODIFIED="1379746094896">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <i>Rationale</i>:
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
<node CREATED="1372909492353" ID="ID_1366862170" MODIFIED="1372909495591" TEXT="&#xb6; 1">
<node CREATED="1372909496450" ID="ID_1114474766" MODIFIED="1372972418839" TEXT="Intuitively, no space is needed for an active tail call because the continuation that is used in the tail call has the same semantics as the continuation passed to the procedure containing the call. "/>
<node CREATED="1372972418841" ID="ID_1714406259" MODIFIED="1372972429020" TEXT="Although an improper implementation might use a new continuation in the call, a return to this new continuation would be followed immediately by a return to the continuation passed to the procedure. "/>
<node CREATED="1372972429022" ID="ID_1309535393" MODIFIED="1372994560185" TEXT="A properly tail-recursive implementation returns to that continuation directly."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372909499297" ID="ID_1332949354" MODIFIED="1372909502271" TEXT="&#xb6; 2">
<node CREATED="1372909510464" ID="ID_1928702064" MODIFIED="1372972434747" TEXT="Proper tail recursion was one of the central ideas in Steele and Sussman&#x2019;s original version of Scheme. "/>
<node CREATED="1372972434748" ID="ID_1501401468" MODIFIED="1372972442593" TEXT="Their first Scheme interpreter implemented both functions and actors. "/>
<node CREATED="1372972442593" ID="ID_1135939228" MODIFIED="1372972455701" TEXT="Control flow was expressed using actors, which differed from functions in that they passed their results on to another actor instead of returning to a caller. "/>
<node CREATED="1372972455703" ID="ID_1564270436" MODIFIED="1372972455705" TEXT="In the terminology of this section, each actor finished with a tail call to another actor."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372909502665" ID="ID_918787298" MODIFIED="1372909503999" TEXT="&#xb6; 3">
<node CREATED="1372909522935" ID="ID_592547433" MODIFIED="1372909523633" TEXT="Steele and Sussman later observed that in their interpreter the code for dealing with actors was identical to that for functions and thus there was no need to include both in the language."/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372909452260" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1927425773" MODIFIED="1379746176763" TEXT="&#xb6; 3">
<node CREATED="1372909556597" ID="ID_775757579" MODIFIED="1372994637564">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      A <font color="#ff0000"><i>tail call</i></font>&#xa0;is a procedure call that occurs in a <i><font color="#ff0000">tail context</font></i>.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372972467813" ID="ID_1817251785" MODIFIED="1372972473587" TEXT="Tail contexts are defined inductively. "/>
<node CREATED="1372972473587" ID="ID_1928711795" MODIFIED="1372972473588" TEXT="Note that a tail context is always determined with respect to a particular lambda expression."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1372909454028" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_357524589" MODIFIED="1379746191226" TEXT="&#xb6; 4">
<node CREATED="1372972510249" ID="ID_1066785698" MODIFIED="1372972514897" TEXT="&#x2022;">
<node CREATED="1372910100626" ID="ID_1170519008" MODIFIED="1372972523767" TEXT="The last expression within the body of a lambda expression, shown as &#x27e8;tail expression&#x27e9; below, occurs in a tail context. "/>
<node CREATED="1372972486427" ID="ID_1952891439" MODIFIED="1372994885981">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      The same is true of all the bodies of <font face="Courier">case-lambda</font>&#xa0;expressions.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
