<node CREATED="1373086723897" ID="ID_270199444" MODIFIED="1373086725127" TEXT="&#xb6; 2">
<node CREATED="1373086807260" ID="ID_1879187517" MODIFIED="1373086968450" TEXT="A procedure call is written by enclosing in parentheses an expression for the procedure to be called followed by expressions for the arguments to be passed to it. "/>
<node CREATED="1373086968452" ID="ID_793133829" MODIFIED="1373086981659" TEXT="The operator and operand expressions are evaluated (in an unspecified order) and the resulting procedure is passed the resulting arguments."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373086725608" ID="ID_813894613" MODIFIED="1373086726727" TEXT="&#xb6; 3">
<node CREATED="1373086825282" ID="ID_1963807742" MODIFIED="1373086872928" TEXT="(+ 3 4) &#x21d2; 7">
<font NAME="Courier" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373086847216" ID="ID_1661818957" MODIFIED="1373086889805" TEXT="((if #f + *) 3 4) &#x21d2; 12">
<font NAME="Courier" SIZE="12"/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373086727056" ID="ID_1876573509" MODIFIED="1373086728671" TEXT="&#xb6; 4">
<node CREATED="1373086899709" ID="ID_910751176" MODIFIED="1373087012316" TEXT="The procedures in this document are available as the values of variables exported by the standard libraries. "/>
<node CREATED="1373087012318" ID="ID_1459934783" MODIFIED="1373087019880" TEXT="For example, the addition and multiplication procedures in the above examples are the values of the variables + and * in the base library. "/>
<node CREATED="1373087019883" ID="ID_1626316293" LINK="#ID_681938213" MODIFIED="1373087080050">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      New procedures are created by evaluating <font face="Courier">lambda</font>&#xa0;expressions (see section 4.1.4).
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373086728960" ID="ID_353994343" MODIFIED="1373086730934" TEXT="&#xb6; 5">
<node CREATED="1373086905948" ID="ID_314316404" LINK="#ID_1617009516" MODIFIED="1373087124767" TEXT="Procedure calls can return any number of values (see values in section 6.10). "/>
<node CREATED="1373087088398" ID="ID_185646537" MODIFIED="1373087145607" TEXT="Most of the procedures defined in this report ">
<node CREATED="1373087145607" ID="ID_856794775" MODIFIED="1373087157285" TEXT="return one value "/>
<node CREATED="1373087157286" ID="ID_1182417585" MODIFIED="1373087157288" TEXT="or, for procedures such as apply, pass on the values returned by a call to one of their arguments. "/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373087095516" ID="ID_674462576" MODIFIED="1373087102716" TEXT="Exceptions are noted in the individual descriptions."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373086731248" ID="ID_614888829" MODIFIED="1373086733118" TEXT="&#xb6; 6">
<node CREATED="1373086911940" ID="ID_476367454" MODIFIED="1373087174803" TEXT="Note:">
<font ITALIC="true" NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1373086914603" ID="ID_171370282" MODIFIED="1373087196285" TEXT="In contrast to other dialects of Lisp, the order of evaluation is unspecified, and the operator expression and the operand expressions are always evaluated with the same evaluation rules."/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373086733600" ID="ID_529720797" MODIFIED="1373086735326" TEXT="&#xb6; 7">
<node CREATED="1373086920571" ID="ID_1677851970" MODIFIED="1373087179003" TEXT="Note:">
<font ITALIC="true" NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1373086923031" ID="ID_1565077266" MODIFIED="1373087206648" TEXT="Although the order of evaluation is otherwise unspecified, the effect of any concurrent evaluation of the operator and operand expressions is constrained to be consistent with some sequential order of evaluation. "/>
<node CREATED="1373087206651" ID="ID_474818926" MODIFIED="1373087206652" TEXT="The order of evaluation may be chosen differently for each procedure call."/>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373086735815" ID="ID_781387395" MODIFIED="1373086737396" TEXT="&#xb6; 8">
<node CREATED="1373086933370" ID="ID_66404206" MODIFIED="1373087182295" TEXT="Note:">
<font ITALIC="true" NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12"/>
<node CREATED="1373086935367" ID="ID_1958567640" MODIFIED="1373087269734">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      In many dialects of Lisp, the empty list, <font face="Courier">()</font>, is a legitimate expression evaluating to itself.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373087232993" ID="ID_1414848356" MODIFIED="1373087252882" TEXT="In Scheme, it is an error.">
<icon BUILTIN="stop-sign"/>
