  <body>
    <p>
      &#x201c;Named <font face="Courier">let</font>&#x201d; is a variant on the syntax of <font face="Courier">let</font>&#xa0;which provides a more general looping construct than <font face="Courier">do</font>&#xa0;and can also be used to express recursion.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374444377650" ID="ID_1363088930" MODIFIED="1374475707817">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      It has the same syntax and semantics as ordinary <font face="Courier">let</font>&#xa0;except that &#x27e8;variable&#x27e9; is bound within &#x27e8;body&#x27e9; to a procedure whose formal arguments are the bound variables and whose body is &#x27e8;body&#x27e9;.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374444390761" ID="ID_549253699" MODIFIED="1374444390762" TEXT="Thus the execution of &#x27e8;body&#x27e9; can be repeated by invoking the procedure named by &#x27e8;variable&#x27e9;."/>
</node>
