<node CREATED="1371765725093" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1534357597" MODIFIED="1379779574025" TEXT="4.3 Macros">
<node CREATED="1374911431008" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_568214139" MODIFIED="1379746818935" TEXT="&#xb6; 1">
<node CREATED="1374911441949" ID="ID_387727604" MODIFIED="1374964417171">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Scheme programs can define and use new derived expression types, called <i><font color="#ff0000">macros</font></i>.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374964382376" ID="ID_1664297922" MODIFIED="1374964525677">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Program-defined expression types have the syntax
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
<node CREATED="1374911466267" ID="ID_54910740" MODIFIED="1374964501560">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <font face="Courier">(</font>&#x27e8;keyword&#x27e9; &#x27e8;datum&#x27e9; ...<font face="Courier">)</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374911497603" ID="ID_782020453" MODIFIED="1374964507164" TEXT="where &#x27e8;keyword&#x27e9; is an identifier that uniquely determines the expression type. "/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374964435055" ID="ID_1215378" MODIFIED="1374964573594">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      This identifier is called the <i><font color="#ff0000">syntactic keyword</font></i>, or simply <i><font color="#ff0000">keyword</font></i>, of the macro.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374964441139" ID="ID_694611327" MODIFIED="1374964473013" TEXT="The number of the &#x27e8;datum&#x27e9;s, and their syntax, depends on the expression type."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374911502058" ID="ID_1521930050" MODIFIED="1379746819351" TEXT="&#xb6; 2">
<node CREATED="1374911510650" ID="ID_745441621" MODIFIED="1374964601083">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Each instance of a macro is called a <i><font color="#ff0000">use</font></i>&#xa0;of the macro.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374964601085" ID="ID_1811861669" MODIFIED="1374964632812">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      The set of rules that specifies how a use of a macro is transcribed into a more primitive expression is called the <i><font color="#ff0000">transformer</font></i>&#xa0;of the macro.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374911513216" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_773772012" MODIFIED="1379746825509" TEXT="&#xb6; 3">
<node CREATED="1374911520664" ID="ID_291704125" MODIFIED="1374911521359" TEXT="The macro definition facility consists of two parts:">
<node CREATED="1374911530641" ID="ID_1187922061" MODIFIED="1374911535438" TEXT="&#x2022;">
<node CREATED="1374911535976" ID="ID_874514355" MODIFIED="1374964662117" TEXT="A set of expressions used to establish that certain identifiers are macro keywords, "/>
<node CREATED="1374964662117" ID="ID_546816711" MODIFIED="1374964669010" TEXT="associate them with macro transformers, "/>
<node CREATED="1374964669010" ID="ID_532392835" MODIFIED="1374964669012" TEXT="and control the scope within which a macro is defined, and"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374911539803" ID="ID_545823303" MODIFIED="1374911542918" TEXT="&#x2022;">
<node CREATED="1374911547310" ID="ID_1675339293" MODIFIED="1374911547868" TEXT="a pattern language for specifying macro transformers."/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374911553261" ID="ID_20187269" MODIFIED="1379746826081" TEXT="&#xb6; 4">
<node CREATED="1374964760362" ID="ID_342199754" MODIFIED="1374964762451" TEXT="">
<node CREATED="1374911560078" ID="ID_1052216412" MODIFIED="1374964757866" TEXT="The syntactic keyword of a macro can shadow variable bindings, "/>
<node CREATED="1374964757866" ID="ID_1984879133" MODIFIED="1374964757868" TEXT="and local variable bindings can shadow syntactic bindings. "/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374964701042" ID="ID_472354973" MODIFIED="1374964701043" TEXT="Two mechanisms are provided to prevent unintended conflicts:">
<node CREATED="1374911566301" ID="ID_256672850" MODIFIED="1374964729360" TEXT="&#x2022;">
<node CREATED="1374911577981" ID="ID_423336613" MODIFIED="1374964797443" TEXT="If ">
<node CREATED="1374964797443" ID="ID_721645668" MODIFIED="1374964806788" TEXT="a macro transformer inserts a binding for an identifier (variable or keyword), "/>
<node CREATED="1374964806788" ID="ID_1651574733" MODIFIED="1374964806790" TEXT="the identifier will in effect be renamed throughout its scope to avoid conflicts with other identifiers. "/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374964785981" ID="ID_880519856" LINK="#ID_1199786640" MODIFIED="1374964821543" TEXT="Note that a global variable definition may or may not introduce a binding; see section 5.3."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374911580148" ID="ID_1905629460" MODIFIED="1374964726198" TEXT="&#x2022;">
<node CREATED="1374911586364" ID="ID_1226929187" MODIFIED="1374964834898" TEXT="If ">
<node CREATED="1374964834898" ID="ID_1713754127" MODIFIED="1374964841048" TEXT="a macro transformer inserts a free reference to an identifier, "/>
<node CREATED="1374964841048" ID="ID_1418003084" MODIFIED="1374964846913" TEXT="the reference refers to the binding that was visible where the transformer was specified, "/>
<node CREATED="1374964846913" ID="ID_729362784" MODIFIED="1374964846915" TEXT="regardless of any local bindings that surround the use of the macro."/>
</node>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374911595116" ID="ID_454175618" MODIFIED="1379746808972" TEXT="&#xb6; 5">
<node CREATED="1374911596832" ID="ID_28770723" MODIFIED="1374964871734" TEXT="In consequence, all macros defined using the pattern language are &#x201c;hygienic&#x201d; and &#x201c;referentially transparent&#x201d; and thus preserve Scheme&#x2019;s lexical scoping. [21, 22, 2, 9, 12]"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374911602292" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_723032511" MODIFIED="1374976557373" TEXT="&#xb6; 6">
<node CREATED="1374911604400" ID="ID_74901307" MODIFIED="1374911604922" TEXT="Implementations may provide macro facilities of other types."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1373599905468" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_225915139" MODIFIED="1379484398443" TEXT="4.3.1 Binding constructs for syntactic keywords">
<node CREATED="1374964901899" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_160731737" MODIFIED="1374970854110" TEXT="&#xb6; 1">
<node CREATED="1374964907338" ID="ID_1715162223" MODIFIED="1374965244668">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      The <font face="Courier">let-syntax</font>&#xa0;and <font face="Courier">letrec-syntax</font>&#xa0;binding constructs are analogous to <font face="Courier">let</font>&#xa0;and <font face="Courier">letrec</font>, but they bind syntactic keywords to macro transformers instead of binding variables to locations that contain values.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1374965244673" ID="ID_361044900" LINK="#ID_1217893537" MODIFIED="1374966002871">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Syntactic keywords can also be bound globally or locally with <font face="Courier">define-syntax</font>; see section 5.4.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
</node>
