<node CREATED="1379207704391" ID="ID_637375713" MODIFIED="1379207707410" TEXT="&#xb6;&#xa0;69">
<node CREATED="1379207752716" ID="ID_1247284314" MODIFIED="1379277503418" TEXT="These procedures compute the usual transcendental functions. "/>
<node CREATED="1379277503418" ID="ID_1417707994" MODIFIED="1379277876655">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      The <font face="Courier">log</font>&#xa0;procedure computes the natural logarithm of <i>z</i>&#xa0; (not the base ten logarithm) if a single argument is given, or the base-<i>z2</i>&#xa0; logarithm of <i>z1</i>&#xa0;if two arguments are given.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1379277510448" ID="ID_1455964924" MODIFIED="1379278049557">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      The <font face="Courier">asin</font>, <font face="Courier">acos</font>, and <font face="Courier">atan</font>&#xa0;procedures compute arcsine (sin^-1), arccosine (cos^-1), and arctangent (tan^-1), respectively.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1379277552407" ID="ID_1919613214" MODIFIED="1379278124091">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      The two-argument variant of atan computes <font face="Courier">(angle (make-rectangular </font><i><font face="SansSerif">x</font></i><font face="Courier">&#xa0; </font><i><font face="SansSerif">y</font></i><font face="Courier">))</font>&#xa0;(see below), even in implementations that don&#x2019;t support complex numbers.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
