  <body>
    <p>
      The <font face="Courier">char-upcase</font>&#xa0;procedure, given an argument that is the lowercase part of a Unicode casing pair, returns the uppercase member of the pair, provided that both characters are supported by the Scheme implementation.&#xa0;
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378013145969" ID="ID_438020126" MODIFIED="1378013207021" TEXT="Note that language-sensitive casing pairs are not used. "/>
<node CREATED="1378013207021" ID="ID_683131577" MODIFIED="1378013207023" TEXT="If the argument is not the lowercase member of such a pair, it is returned."/>
</node>
