<node CREATED="1378527886229" ID="ID_203962255" MODIFIED="1378527887548" TEXT="&#xb6; 48">
<node CREATED="1378527894844" ID="ID_402679020" MODIFIED="1378566229879">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Calls <i>thunk</i>&#xa0;without arguments, returning the result(s) of this call.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378566229881" ID="ID_199334044" MODIFIED="1378566234743">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <i>Before</i>&#xa0;and <i>after</i>&#xa0;are called, also without arguments, as required by the following rules.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378566234744" ID="ID_1362451592" MODIFIED="1378566240346">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Note that, in the absence of calls to continuations captured using <font face="Courier">call-with-current-continuation</font>, the three arguments are called once each, in order.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378566240349" ID="ID_1358475628" MODIFIED="1378566246576">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <i>Before</i>&#xa0;is called whenever execution enters the dynamic extent of the call to <i>thunk</i>&#xa0;&#xa0;and <i>after</i>&#xa0;is called whenever it exits that dynamic extent.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378566246579" ID="ID_27152061" MODIFIED="1378566251575">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      The dynamic extent of a procedure call is the period between when the call is initiated and when it returns.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378566251578" ID="ID_480835665" MODIFIED="1378566256398">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      The <i>before</i>&#xa0;and <i>after</i>&#xa0;&#xa0;thunks are called in the same dynamic environment as the call to <font face="Courier">dynamic-wind</font>.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378566257148" ID="ID_1818011602" MODIFIED="1378566262946">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      In Scheme, because of <font face="Courier">call-with-current-continuation</font>, the dynamic extent of a call is not always a single, connected time period.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378566262948" ID="ID_1692386771" MODIFIED="1378566321402">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      It is defined as follows:
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378527972160" ID="ID_1995333924" MODIFIED="1378527974549" TEXT="&#xb6; 49">
<node CREATED="1378527994759" ID="ID_18929444" MODIFIED="1378527998014" TEXT="&#x2022; The dynamic extent is entered when execution of the body of the called procedure begins."/>
<node CREATED="1378528009805" ID="ID_1639215473" MODIFIED="1378566350022">
<richcontent TYPE="NODE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      &#x2022; The dynamic extent is also entered when execution is not within the dynamic extent and a continuation is invoked that was captured (using <font face="Courier">call-with-current-continuation</font>) during the dynamic extent.
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
</node>
<node CREATED="1378528024428" ID="ID_817706832" MODIFIED="1378528035211" TEXT="&#x2022; It is exited when the called procedure returns."/>
<node CREATED="1378528049154" ID="ID_433997647" MODIFIED="1378528052506" TEXT="&#x2022; It is also exited when execution is within the dynamic extent and a continuation is invoked that was captured while not within the dynamic extent."/>
</node>
