<node CREATED="1375253382596" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1257822937" MODIFIED="1379399359723" TEXT="&#xb6;&#xa0;5">
<node CREATED="1375253389460" ID="ID_177814564" MODIFIED="1379394674296" TEXT="In addition to the identifier characters of the ASCII repertoire specified below, Scheme implementations may permit any additional repertoire of Unicode characters to be employed in identifiers, provided that each such character has a Unicode general category of Lu, Ll, Lt, Lm, Lo, Mn, Mc, Me, Nd, Nl, No, Pd, Pc, Po, Sc, Sm, Sk, So, or Co, or is U+200C or U+200D (the zero-width non-joiner and joiner, respectively, which are needed for correct spelling in Persian, Hindi, and other languages). "/>
<node CREATED="1379394674298" ID="ID_920555052" MODIFIED="1379394681463" TEXT="However, it is an error for the first character to have a general category of Nd, Mc, or Me. "/>
<node CREATED="1379394681463" ID="ID_705539750" MODIFIED="1379394681465" TEXT="It is also an error to use a non-Unicode character in symbols or identifiers."/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1375253397579" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1124435002" MODIFIED="1379399360049" TEXT="&#xb6;&#xa0;6">
