<node CREATED="1377154334784" ID="ID_968627792" MODIFIED="1377154431925" TEXT="The division between the base library and the other standard libraries is ">
<node CREATED="1377154431926" ID="ID_1119511882" MODIFIED="1377154439642" TEXT="based on use, "/>
<node CREATED="1377154439643" ID="ID_1743017135" MODIFIED="1377154439644" TEXT="not on construction. "/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1377154345323" ID="ID_1159979949" MODIFIED="1377154455313" TEXT="In particular, some facilities that are typically implemented as primitives by a compiler or the run-time system rather than in terms of other standard procedures or syntax are ">
<node CREATED="1377154455316" ID="ID_267692650" MODIFIED="1377154464355" TEXT="not part of the base library, "/>
<node CREATED="1377154464356" ID="ID_1279080973" MODIFIED="1377154464356" TEXT="but are defined in separate libraries. "/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1377154353403" ID="ID_1044853354" MODIFIED="1377154359655" TEXT="By the same token, some exports of the base library are implementable in terms of other exports. "/>
<node CREATED="1377154359656" ID="ID_1118258319" MODIFIED="1377154359657" TEXT="They are redundant in the strict sense of the word, but they capture common patterns of usage, and are therefore provided as convenient abbreviations."/>
</node>
